<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI COMMITTEE TO PUSH FOR REVITALIZATION OF DANSHUI RIVER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan. 23 (CNA) 01/23/07  21:37:40 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
An interdepartmental meeting of the Taipei city government
approved Tuesday a proposal to set up a committee that will
supervise a project to clean and revitalize the polluted Danshui
river, which runs through the western district of the city.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the proposal,  presented  by the city
government's Public Works Department, experts and scholars would
be invited to join senior city government officials on the
committee, headed by Taipei Mayor Hau Lung-bin.
</P>
<P>
Hau told the meeting that one of his promises during his election
campaign was to clean and revitalize the river.
</P>
<P>
He said the committee will meet once per month to review the
progress of the project, while subgroups under the committee in
charge of different programs will meet once every two weeks.
</P>
<P>
City government officials on the committee will come from the
Public Works Department, the Department of Transportation, the
Department  of Environmental Protection and the Department of
Information.
</P>
<P>
The plan to revitalize the Danshui will not only try to improve
the water quality of the river, but will also create landscapes
and areas for leisure activities along the riverbanks, according
to the Department of Public Works.
</P>
<P>
The mayor expressed confidence that the project will be completed
in four years.
</P>
